.TH HN 1 "2026" "The-JLC-Project" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hn \- show or set the system hostname
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hn
.RI [ name ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hn
with no arguments prints the current hostname to standard output.
With a
.I name
argument it sets the system hostname using
.BR sethostname (2).
Setting the hostname requires appropriate privileges (typically root).
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
.BR gethostname (2)
or
.BR sethostname (2)
failed.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Print the current hostname:
.B hn
.TP
Set the hostname:
.EX
hn mybox
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR hostname (1),
.BR uname (1)
.SH AUTHORS
The-JLC-Project contributors.
